A weathered craftsman's woodworking workshop in Studio Ghibli style, warm afternoon light streaming through dusty windows onto a worn wooden workbench scattered with hand tools—chisels, planes, and mallets. In the foreground, rough wooden blocks in various stages of transformation: raw timber, partially carved pieces, and one beautifully finished smooth sculpture. Soft golden dust particles float in the sunbeams. Shelves lined with completed masterworks in the background, showing progression of skill. The atmosphere is nostalgic and contemplative, with rich earth tones of amber, brown, and cream. Gentle shadows and that distinctive Ghibli soft-focus quality, conveying the patient journey from novice to expert through visible stages of craftsmanship.
